The paper deals with privacy-preserving algorithms for near-neighbor search on large datasets, which involves topics related to cryptography (cs.CR), data structures (cs.DS), databases (cs.DB), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on the development of a new algorithm for secure locality-sensitive indexing, which is a combination of techniques from these different areas. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CR, cs.DS, and cs.DB, followed by cs.IT and cs.LG.
